 0f406597-62d9-4fea-944b-6c77e9b1cf5e.56ed1d9b-fdf1-4867-89e2-bab59a870eac.description=Purpose\: 
 Gather all the optional parameters for a standalone SQL Server install. All advanced parameters are hidden in the deployment screen by default. In order to activate an advanced parameter, go into the Workflow, and change the parameter mapping from on this step from "Blank" to "User

 SQL Agent Password - *Required if SQL Agent Account is specified and not a built-in account.
 SQL Service Account - Optional. Specifies the login account for the SQL Server service. Can be a local Windows user, a domain user, or a built-in account (ie. NT AUTHORITY\NETWORK SERVICE). If not a built-in account, ensure corresponding password is provided.

 0f406597-62d9-4fea-944b-6c77e9b1cf5e.5c655780-25db-4d12-8c4e-a4b8a84b11ed.description=Create an installation template file (.INI file) for installing SQL Server 2008. Template files enable unattended installation/upgrades of SQL Server 2008 to be run by providing service account and other information to the command-line setup program. This step verifies that all required parameters are provided, and writes any optional parameters to the template file if they are non-blank.


Inputs\:
 command - executes MSSQLCreateInstallorUpgradeTemplate.py
 Action - *REQUIRED. Provisioning action to be performed. Acceptable values are Install, Cluster Install, Add Cluster Node, or Upgrade
 Additional Template Parameters - Optional. Pipe-delimited ("|") list of additional template parameters and values. Should follow this example\: SQMREPORTING|1|INSTANCEDIR|"D\:\SQLDirectory"
 Backup Directory - No description
 Cluster Administrator Account - *Required, for cluster operations only. Domain user that will run the setup operation; requires elevated administrator privileges on the cluster. Acceptable value is in format [DOMAIN]\[USERNAME]
 Cluster Administrator Password - *Required, for cluster operations only. Does not apply for standalone installs. Password for the domain user that will run the setup operation; requires elevated administrator privileges on the cluster. Must be a strong Windows password.
 Cluster Node Names - *Required, for SQL 05 cluster install only. Does not apply for all other installs. Comma-delimited list of node members' hostnames. Acceptable format\: [Node1Hostname],[Node2Hostname]
 Data File Location - *Required for SQL 05 cluster install only. Optional parameter for all other installs. Specifies the location for the SQL Server data files.
 Database Data Directory - No description
 Database Log Directory - No description
 Failover Cluster Disks - No description
 Install Components - Optional. A comma-delimited list that specifies which components to install. Feature names are case sensitive. For a list of components for SQL 08 R2 (as well as links to previous versions), go here\: http\://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms144259(v\=SQL.105).aspx\#Feature
 Installation Path - *Required for SQL 05 cluster install only. Optional parameter for all other installs. Specifies the location for the SQL Server program files.
 Instance Name - *REQUIRED. Specifies a SQL Server instance name for the instance that is being installed/upgraded. Use "MSSQLSERVER" for default instance, or any name of up to 16 alphanumeric characters for named instances.
 Path to Setup Files - *REQUIRED. Path to directory where SQL Server's setup.exe file is located.
 Product Key - Optional. Specifies the product key for the edition of SQL Server. If this parameter is not specified, Evaluation is used.
 Public IP Address - *Required, for SQL 05 cluster install only. Not for any other type of installs. Specify the IP address for the newly created SQL cluster. Must be an address not in use on a public domain.
 Public IP Network Name - *Required, for SQL 05 cluster install only. Not for any other type of installs. Specify the name of the public network that the cluster will be installed on. The Public IP Address will be created on this network
 SA Password - Optional. Specifies the password for the SQL Server sa account. If specified, security mode will be set to SQL authentication. If left blank, security mode will be set to Windows authentication.
 SQL Agent Account - *REQUIRED. Specifies the login account for the SQL Server Agent service. Can be a local Windows user, a domain user, or a built-in account (ie. NT AUTHORITY\NETWORK SERVICE). If not a built-in account, ensure corresponding password is provided.
 SQL Agent Domain Group - *Required, for SQL 05 cluster installs. Optional for all other cluster installs. Specifies the domain group that the SQL Agent Account user is a member of.
 SQL Agent Password - *Required if SQL Agent Account is not a built-in account.
 SQL Browser Account - *Required, for SQL 05 installs only. Optional for all other types of installs. Specifies the login account for the SQL Server Agent service. Can be a local Windows user, a domain user, or a built-in account (ie. NT AUTHORITY\NETWORK SERVICE). If not a built-in account, ensure corresponding password is provided.
 SQL Browser Password - *Required if SQL Browser Account not a built-in account.
 SQL Cluster Domain Group - *Required, for SQL 05 cluster installs only. Optional for all other cluster installs. Specifies the domain group that the SQL Service Account user is a member of.
 SQL Cluster Resource Group - *Required, for SQL 05 cluster installs only. Optional for all other cluster installs. The name of the cluster resource group where the SQL cluster will be installed. This cluster group should already be created by a system administrator. The cluster resource group will have the shared disks that the SQL data files and shared program files will be stored.
 SQL Cluster Shared Directory - *Required, for SQL 05 cluster installs only. Optional for all other cluster installs. Specifies the path to the directory where shared cluster program files will be stored. Must be on a disk shared by all nodes of the cluster.
 SQL Collation - Optional. Specifies the collation of the instance. If left blank, the instance will be installed with the collation of the OS.
 SQL Service Account - *REQUIRED. Specifies the login account for the SQL Server service. Can be a local Windows user, a domain user, or a built-in account (ie. NT AUTHORITY\NETWORK SERVICE). If not a built-in account, ensure corresponding password is provided.
 SQL Service Password - *Required if SQL Service Account not a built-in account.
 SQL Sysadmin Accounts - *Required, for SQL 08 and 08 R2 installs. Not applicable for SQL 05. A comma-delimited list of user accounts that will be set as system administrators. Each account must either be a local Windows user or a domain user.
 TempDB Data Directory - No description
 TempDB Log Directory - No description
 Update Source - No description
 Server.Name - No description
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Cluster Administrator Account - No description
 Cluster Administrator Password - No description
 SQL Version - No description
 Template File - Full path to the newly created template file (ie. C\:\\template.ini)
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 0f406597-62d9-4fea-944b-6c77e9b1cf5e.d40bfd37-b6a4-42dc-bbcd-5295dcf7b04c.description=77b27936-ab2b-4dea-8618-b33435118687.6efa46f5-44ea-4e60-8766-610c60b5c04d.description 0f406597-62d9-4fea-944b-6c77e9b1cf5e.description=<pre>
 Description

This workflow installs a new standalone instance of SQL Server 2008/2008 R2/2012/2014 on an already existing Windows 2003/2008/2008 R2/2012/2012 R2 server. The default deployment will only show required parameters.

 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Cluster Administrator Account - No description
 Cluster Administrator Password - No description
 Download Target Destination - *Required. The local directory where the SQL Setup files should be stored.
 Instance Name - *Required. The name of the newly created instance. Use "MSSQLSERVER" for the default instance, any other alphanumeric value for a named instance. *Optional, String. Default value \= MSSQLSERVER (default instance)
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 Server.Name - No description

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Additional Template Parameters - Optional. Pipe-delimited ("|") list of additional template parameters and values. Should follow this example\: SQMREPORTING|1|INSTANCEDIR|"D\:\SQLDirectory"
 Product Key - Optional. Specifies the product key for the edition of SQL Server. If this parameter is not specified, Evaluation is used.
 SQL Instance Password - Optional\: If default Windows user is unable to login to instance, specify password to either a Windows or SQL user that can login.
 Skip Simulation - Optional. If set to "YES", workflow will skip Simulate step and proceed directly to install/upgrade step
 SQL Instance Account - Optional\: If default Windows user is unable to login to instance, specify either a Windows or SQL user that can login.
 Installer Password - Optional - The password of the Windows account that will be performing the installation
 Download From Software Directory - Optional. The name of the ZIP file containing the SQL Server setup files
 Installer Account - Optional - The Windows account that will be performing the installation.

 Dependencies

SQL Server 2008/2008 R2/2012/2014 installation media must be mounted prior to running this workflow.

 Results Verification

- In the last step, the workflow verifies that SQL Server standalone instance is currently installed.
- Run "SELECT @@VERSION" against the SQL Server Instance to ensure that version 10.0 (SQL 2008), 10.50 (SQL 2008 R2), 11.0 (SQL 2012), or 12.0 (SQL 2014) is returned.



 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
</pre> 0f406597-62d9-4fea-944b-6c77e9b1cf5e.f3444c38-c076-4181-bb00-88ba3e6e054c.description=This step is designed to facilitate the complicated methodologies that various companies use to distribute their software bundles for installation.
